15
00:02:13,183 --> 00:02:14,644
First of all, quit this job immediately.

16
00:02:14,644 --> 00:02:16,436
Don't worry about me.

17
00:02:16,436 --> 00:02:18,998
Just go home.

18
00:02:28,778 --> 00:02:30,570
You're Seo Je Yi from Class Two, right?

19
00:02:30,570 --> 00:02:32,311
Aren't you Ro Bin's older brother?

20
00:02:32,311 --> 00:02:35,174
And you didn't know Ro Bin worked here?

21
00:02:36,456 --> 00:02:38,668
Hey, are you listening to me?

22
00:02:38,668 --> 00:02:40,370
So he can't tell anyone.

23
00:02:40,370 --> 00:02:43,292
And if we want to clear his name, we need to find the real culprit.

24
00:02:43,292 --> 00:02:45,966
We can do that. Don't worry too much.

25
00:02:45,966 --> 00:02:47,267
Let's go.

26
00:02:48,128 --> 00:02:50,329
Hey!

27
00:02:50,329 --> 00:02:53,432
Hey! Are you ignoring me?

28
00:02:53,432 --> 00:02:55,585
Hey, Oh Ji Na!

29
00:03:02,142 --> 00:03:05,153
Who could have taken Ju Ri's wallet?

30
00:03:07,778 --> 00:03:11,631
I wish Revenge Note could tell me who the culprit is.

31
00:03:34,304 --> 00:03:36,056
Revenge Note,

32
00:03:36,056 --> 00:03:38,458
tell me who the culprit is.

33
00:03:43,934 --> 00:03:46,215
Of course it doesn't work that way.

34
00:03:59,749 --> 00:04:02,543
Hanjong High School

35
00:04:14,764 --> 00:04:16,556
He's shameless.

36
00:04:22,933 --> 00:04:24,434
Hi.

37
00:04:27,476 --> 00:04:28,857
Hey.

38
00:04:29,820 --> 00:04:32,401
You don't care even if he's a thief?

39
00:04:32,401 --> 00:04:33,933
You still like him?

40
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:35,476
It isn't him.

41
00:04:35,476 --> 00:04:37,197
He's being falsely accused.

42
00:04:37,197 --> 00:04:39,580
She's totally blinded by love.

43
00:04:39,580 --> 00:04:42,792
- She's calling a thief innocent.
- Do you guys have a death wish?

44
00:04:42,792 --> 00:04:46,024
The only thing Ro Bin stole

45
00:04:46,024 --> 00:04:48,417
is my heart.

46
00:04:48,417 --> 00:04:50,600
She's totally lost it.

47
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:53,012
There's no cure for this.

48
00:04:55,384 --> 00:04:56,946
You're okay, right?

49
00:04:57,807 --> 00:04:59,158
Everyone,

50
00:04:59,158 --> 00:05:02,061
they already made the t-shirts.

51
00:05:02,061 --> 00:05:06,065
So we can't cancel the order and we have to send the money by tonight.

52
00:05:06,065 --> 00:05:08,478
Let's just collect the money again.

53
00:05:08,478 --> 00:05:11,111
Even if you don't have money, try to borrow some.

54
00:05:11,111 --> 00:05:13,423
- You want us to pay 20,000 won (≈$180) again?
- Why do we have to pay?

55
00:05:13,423 --> 00:05:16,596
Class President, make the thief pay for it.

56
00:05:16,596 --> 00:05:20,580
We'll get the money back once we catch the thief.

57
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:23,593
- Let's just collect it again.
- But we already caught him.

58
00:05:23,593 --> 00:05:25,665
We clearly know who did it.

59
00:05:25,665 --> 00:05:28,838
It's ridiculous that the whole class has to suffer.

60
00:05:28,838 --> 00:05:31,259
- Ro Bin didn't do it.
- Ro Bin didn't do it.

61
00:05:33,422 --> 00:05:35,744
- There's no proof.
- There's no proof.

62
00:05:37,677 --> 00:05:40,189
- You can't do that.
- You can't do that.

63
00:05:43,102 --> 00:05:47,047
I heard that there was exactly 400,000 won (≈ $360) in the envelope Ro Bin had.

64
00:05:47,047 --> 00:05:48,887
What do you think now?

65
00:05:53,023 --> 00:05:54,813
Everyone, stop.

66
00:05:55,526 --> 00:05:58,709
Don't treat Ro Bin like that.

67
00:05:58,709 --> 00:06:01,720
It might not be someone from our class.

68
00:06:02,783 --> 00:06:05,494
It's my fault for losing it and not managing it better.

69
00:06:05,494 --> 00:06:08,878
Why is that your fault? You're the victim here.

70
00:06:08,878 --> 00:06:11,060
We all didn't want to collect it,

71
00:06:11,060 --> 00:06:12,422
and you took charge and did it.

72
00:06:12,422 --> 00:06:15,425
She's right. It doesn't matter who collected it.

73
00:06:15,425 --> 00:06:17,066
That person would have stolen it anyway.

74
00:06:17,066 --> 00:06:18,598
Don't worry about it.

75
00:06:20,089 --> 00:06:22,732
Gosh, this is so annoying.

76
00:06:26,095 --> 00:06:27,946
Don't worry about it.

77
00:06:33,232 --> 00:06:35,033
She's so scary.

78
00:06:36,196 --> 00:06:37,818
- Pass the ball!
- Give him the ball.

79
00:06:37,818 --> 00:06:39,238
- Pass it.
- Pass the ball.

80
00:06:39,238 --> 00:06:41,139
- Over here.
- Pass it.

81
00:06:46,076 --> 00:06:47,628
Come on!

82
00:06:47,628 --> 00:06:49,288
Why are they playing by themselves?

83
00:06:49,288 --> 00:06:51,411
- They should've passed it.
- I know.

84
00:06:59,549 --> 00:07:00,880
Come out.

85
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:03,012
What's going on? What's wrong with them?

86
00:07:03,012 --> 00:07:04,584
Catch it!

87
00:07:04,584 --> 00:07:06,936
You need to pass it to Ro Bin.

88
00:07:06,936 --> 00:07:09,149
You're not going to score playing like that.

89
00:07:10,189 --> 00:07:12,221
My gosh.

90
00:07:16,236 --> 00:07:20,189
But how did Su Ji know where to find Ro Bin?

91
00:07:21,862 --> 00:07:24,664
Pass it here. Pass...

92
00:07:32,372 --> 00:07:34,405
- Who did that?
- Sorry.

93
00:07:34,405 --> 00:07:36,465
My hand slipped.

94
00:07:41,090 --> 00:07:43,342
This is so frustrating.

95
00:07:43,342 --> 00:07:45,224
Try using your brains.

96
00:07:45,224 --> 00:07:49,128
If there's a thief on the team, how is that going to look to the others?

97
00:07:49,128 --> 00:07:52,161
What do you think?

98
00:07:52,161 --> 00:07:54,024
So what do you want us to do?

99
00:07:54,024 --> 00:07:56,146
What I'm saying is...

100
00:07:56,146 --> 00:07:58,857
Let's pull him off the team.

101
00:08:00,030 --> 00:08:01,471
I'm against that.

102
00:08:01,471 --> 00:08:03,684
Could we even win without Ro Bin?

103
00:08:03,684 --> 00:08:05,544
He's the ace of the team.

104
00:08:05,544 --> 00:08:06,657
What are you talking about?

105
00:08:06,657 --> 00:08:08,158
I'm here. Don't you trust me?

106
00:08:08,158 --> 00:08:10,329
That's right, An Mi Nam.

107
00:08:10,329 --> 00:08:13,051
We can totally win without Ro Bin on the team.

108
00:08:13,051 --> 00:08:14,734
Let's take a vote.

109
00:08:14,734 --> 00:08:17,748
Raise your hand if you're against pulling Ro Bin off.

110
00:08:22,882 --> 00:08:24,004
It's over.

111
00:08:25,305 --> 00:08:27,767
You see this, right?

112
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:29,329
You're out.

113
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,470
Okay, then.

114
00:08:31,470 --> 00:08:33,223
Ha Sweong Su, you're in.

115
00:08:33,223 --> 00:08:36,025
Really? All right!

116
00:08:36,025 --> 00:08:37,707
You'll do good, right?

117
00:08:47,156 --> 00:08:49,778
Whoever didn't pay for the shirts, pay up.

118
00:08:50,580 --> 00:08:51,772
Come on.

119
00:08:51,772 --> 00:08:55,294
Class President, I'll pay next time.

120
00:08:55,294 --> 00:08:57,296
- Here you go.
- That's for me.

121
00:08:57,296 --> 00:08:59,818
- This is Ha Jun's.
- Okay.

122
00:09:04,343 --> 00:09:05,856
That's right.

123
00:09:05,856 --> 00:09:08,266
I used my money at the cafeteria.

124
00:09:14,515 --> 00:09:16,255
Hey, Ju Ri.

125
00:09:16,255 --> 00:09:20,058
Sorry, but could you lend me 10,000 won (≈ $9)? I'll pay you back tomorrow.

126
00:09:21,731 --> 00:09:23,432
Sure.

127
00:09:25,945 --> 00:09:27,486
Thanks.

128
00:09:35,705 --> 00:09:37,206
What is this?

129
00:09:38,789 --> 00:09:40,339
Where's my money?

130
00:09:46,135 --> 00:09:48,217
Is this...

131
00:09:48,217 --> 00:09:50,782
Ji Na, what are you up to?

132
00:09:50,782 --> 00:09:53,102
- Come with me.
- Me?

133
00:09:55,645 --> 00:09:57,827
So this is the money you paid?

134
00:09:57,827 --> 00:09:59,690
I think so.

135
00:09:59,690 --> 00:10:00,691
Look at this.

136
00:10:00,691 --> 00:10:03,313
When I paid this, this exact mark was on the bill.

137
00:10:03,313 --> 00:10:05,764
Why did Ju Ri have that?

138
00:10:07,617 --> 00:10:11,320
Do you think goody two-shoes Ju Ri stole this?

139
00:10:12,782 --> 00:10:15,284
Everyone, stop.

140
00:10:15,284 --> 00:10:18,528
Don't treat Ro Bin like that.

141
00:10:21,712 --> 00:10:24,003
Your notes are definitely something else.

142
00:10:24,003 --> 00:10:26,345
They're awesome.

143
00:10:28,047 --> 00:10:29,599
I'm not too sure.

144
00:10:29,599 --> 00:10:33,092
The money I paid was definitely stolen.

145
00:10:33,092 --> 00:10:35,325
But why does Ju Ri have it?

146
00:10:35,325 --> 00:10:37,306
So Ju Ri pocketed the money,

147
00:10:37,306 --> 00:10:40,198
and she made it look like someone stole it.

148
00:10:41,231 --> 00:10:45,314
Then this should be proof that will clear Ro Bin's name, right?

149
00:10:45,314 --> 00:10:47,357
- No.
- Why not?

150
00:10:47,357 --> 00:10:50,279
You're just saying that mark is yours.

151
00:10:50,279 --> 00:10:53,051
What if they say you're lying because you're Ro Bin's friend?

152
00:10:54,203 --> 00:10:57,516
We need more solid proof.

153
00:10:57,516 --> 00:10:59,099
Jeong Bo Ra.

154
00:10:59,099 --> 00:11:01,040
You have that video you took during gym class, right?

155
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,682
I do. Why?

156
00:11:02,682 --> 00:11:05,174
The teacher wants you to edit it to upload on the school website.

157
00:11:05,174 --> 00:11:07,426
Okay. When does he want it?

158
00:11:07,426 --> 00:11:10,168
Right away. Edit it and send it.

159
00:11:11,591 --> 00:11:13,852
Let's go to the computer room for now.

160
00:11:14,724 --> 00:11:16,166
This is your last chance.

161
00:11:16,166 --> 00:11:19,858
Tell me where you worked to get this money.

162
00:11:20,891 --> 00:11:22,372
You little brat.

163
00:11:22,372 --> 00:11:24,044
Will you keep doing this?

164
00:11:24,044 --> 00:11:25,855
I didn't steal it.

165
00:11:25,855 --> 00:11:27,857
Seo Ro Bin...

166
00:11:27,857 --> 00:11:29,430
That's why

167
00:11:29,430 --> 00:11:32,402
I'm telling you to tell me where you worked to get this money.

168
00:11:32,402 --> 00:11:34,022
Teacher!

169
00:11:37,997 --> 00:11:39,660
He really did earn that money.

170
00:11:39,660 --> 00:11:42,622
I can't tell you the details now, but it definitelywasn't Ro Bin.

171
00:11:42,622 --> 00:11:44,765
But the proof is all there.

172
00:11:44,765 --> 00:11:47,106
If you admit your wrongdoings now and reflect on yourself,

173
00:11:47,106 --> 00:11:49,519
we could end this with just some school clean-up.

174
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:53,053
If you don't come clean, this could go to the disciplinary council.

175
00:11:53,053 --> 00:11:54,873
Do you want that?

176
00:11:57,977 --> 00:11:59,179
Go on.

177
00:11:59,179 --> 00:12:01,370
Let's talk next time.

178
00:12:11,321 --> 00:12:13,122
Mr. Lee.

179
00:12:20,369 --> 00:12:23,122
- I told you not to say anything.
- Just tell them about the club.

180
00:12:23,122 --> 00:12:24,564
That's better than being a thief.

181
00:12:24,564 --> 00:12:26,086
I told you I can't.

182
00:12:26,086 --> 00:12:29,669
I don't want the club to suffer because of me.

183
00:12:29,669 --> 00:12:32,711
I'd rather drop out of school.

184
00:12:35,384 --> 00:12:37,046
Hey!

185
00:12:46,476 --> 00:12:47,927
So you're saying

186
00:12:47,927 --> 00:12:51,280
that this is all a fabricated story that Ju Ri made up?

187
00:12:51,280 --> 00:12:52,552
I think so.

188
00:12:52,552 --> 00:12:55,905
She definitely had her wallet up until gym class that day.

189
00:12:56,696 --> 00:13:00,559
But I have no idea when she pocketed it.

190
00:13:06,165 --> 00:13:09,379
Bo Ra, this is the video that you took during gym class, right?

191
00:13:09,379 --> 00:13:11,210
It is.

192
00:13:11,210 --> 00:13:13,133
But I didn't film just our classmates.

193
00:13:13,133 --> 00:13:15,285
But this video could help us out.

194
00:13:15,285 --> 00:13:17,065
I'll take a look at it.

195
00:13:33,322 --> 00:13:34,694
It's as we thought.

196
00:13:34,694 --> 00:13:36,527
We can't tell just by this video.

197
00:13:36,527 --> 00:13:39,989
I didn't keep filming the bleachers.

198
00:13:39,989 --> 00:13:41,120
Wait a minute.

199
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:42,451
- What?
- What?

200
00:13:42,451 --> 00:13:43,853
At first,

201
00:13:43,853 --> 00:13:46,626
there's no water bottle near Ju Ri.

202
00:13:46,626 --> 00:13:49,589
But here, there's a water bottle near her.

203
00:13:54,343 --> 00:13:57,156
So during gym class, Ju Ri went back to the classroom

204
00:13:57,156 --> 00:13:58,698
for a water bottle?

205
00:13:58,698 --> 00:14:00,850
If she went there and back,

206
00:14:00,850 --> 00:14:03,723
then she had time to hide the wallet.

207
00:14:03,723 --> 00:14:05,795
But why would Ju Ri do that?

208
00:14:05,795 --> 00:14:07,356
She's a model student.

209
00:14:07,356 --> 00:14:08,758
I know, right?

210
00:14:08,758 --> 00:14:11,311
This is so shocking.

211
00:14:11,311 --> 00:14:14,162
That might not be her true self.

212
00:14:15,865 --> 00:14:18,528
Let's find out

213
00:14:18,528 --> 00:14:20,359
why she did it.

214
00:14:29,830 --> 00:14:33,823
Baek Ju Ri

215
00:14:33,823 --> 00:14:37,256
I didn't know Ju Ri was into designer brands.

216
00:14:37,256 --> 00:14:40,269
You can't buy a designer-brand wallet for only 400,000 won.

217
00:14:41,140 --> 00:14:42,593
What about a used one?

218
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:01,100
Luxury bag for sale!!!

219
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,700
Oooh!

220
00:15:08,457 --> 00:15:10,419
Baek Ju Ri, I'll send you the money right now

221
00:15:10,419 --> 00:15:13,874
She wrote that she wanted to buy a designer brand bag a few days ago.

222
00:15:13,874 --> 00:15:17,326
She even wrote that she was buying it on the day the wallet disappeared.

223
00:15:17,326 --> 00:15:20,360
She did all of this just for a bag?

224
00:15:21,632 --> 00:15:23,463
No way.

225
00:15:28,848 --> 00:15:30,690
Give me a second.

226
00:15:39,318 --> 00:15:40,970
Does this mean

227
00:15:40,970 --> 00:15:44,034
that the culprit is Ju Ri for sure?

228
00:15:44,034 --> 00:15:46,555
Isn't he the guy who stole the money for the class shirts?

229
00:15:46,555 --> 00:15:48,408
You wouldn't suspect it from that face.

230
00:15:48,408 --> 00:15:49,660
Make the thief pay for it.

231
00:15:49,660 --> 00:15:51,721
He's got no conscience.

232
00:15:51,721 --> 00:15:53,552
I guess he doesn't care.

233
00:15:58,257 --> 00:15:59,550
That's right.

234
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:02,891
I can't let Ro Bin continue to be accused of stealing.

235
00:16:05,134 --> 00:16:08,107
Will you be the Revenge Goddess?

236
00:16:10,180 --> 00:16:11,211
Enter target's name

237
00:16:11,211 --> 00:16:13,352
Baek Ju Ri

238
00:16:13,352 --> 00:16:16,086
Target meets all conditions.
We will proceed with the revenge.

239
00:16:25,946 --> 00:16:30,039
But we can't clear Ro Bin's name with just this alone.

240
00:16:30,039 --> 00:16:32,603
We need solid proof that Ju Ri is the culprit.

241
00:16:32,603 --> 00:16:35,505
That's right. What should we do?

242
00:16:42,462 --> 00:16:44,595
How about this?

243
00:16:44,595 --> 00:16:46,346
Everyone.

244
00:16:46,346 --> 00:16:48,117
Did you hear?

245
00:16:48,117 --> 00:16:51,221
Teacher Maeng said that if the money doesn't show up by tomorrow,

246
00:16:51,221 --> 00:16:53,073
she's going to call the police.

247
00:16:53,073 --> 00:16:54,373
Really?

248
00:16:54,373 --> 00:16:57,667
If the police come, they'll play the security camera footage.

249
00:16:57,667 --> 00:16:59,418
Then they'll find the culprit right away.

250
00:16:59,418 --> 00:17:01,581
What a relief. I hope they find the person quickly.

251
00:17:01,581 --> 00:17:04,735
My dad knows a ton of people in the police.

252
00:17:04,735 --> 00:17:06,336
Should I tell my dad?

253
00:17:06,336 --> 00:17:09,009
Whoever it is must be shaking in their shoes right now.

254
00:17:09,009 --> 00:17:12,482
If we catch the culprit, we'll all get our money back.

255
00:17:12,482 --> 00:17:14,223
What if the culprit spent it all already?

256
00:17:14,223 --> 00:17:17,697
Ju Ri, isn't that a relief? Now you don't have to worry.

257
00:17:17,697 --> 00:17:20,601
I know. What a relief.

258
00:17:20,601 --> 00:17:23,252
I hope they catch the culprit soon.

259
00:17:24,354 --> 00:17:26,566
- What a relief.
- Yes.

260
00:17:26,566 --> 00:17:28,819
You have been selected as a revenge target.

261
00:17:28,819 --> 00:17:30,899
"Revenge target"?

262
00:17:37,518 --> 00:17:39,919
What is this? Who could have sent this?

263
00:17:39,919 --> 00:17:43,724
You have been selected as a revenge target.

264
00:17:43,724 --> 00:17:46,276
- I'm so hungry.
- I know, right?

265
00:17:46,276 --> 00:17:47,577
This calls for tteokbokki.*
(rice cakes in spicy sauce)

